K and 350 K, and makes it too\nhot to be in the habitable zone. At a distance of only 2.5 pc, Gl411 b, is the\nthird closest low-mass planet detected to date. Its proximity to Earth will\npermit probing its atmosphere with a combination of high-contrast imaging and\nhigh-dispersion spectroscopy in the next decade.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 15 Feb 2019 23:13:41 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 26 Mar 2019 18:51:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-05-01"}
